<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-12703] Allow unencrypted private keys when using PEM files</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-12703</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Unencrypted PEM files seem to be internally &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/blob/a46beb9d29781e0709baf596601122f770a5fa31/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/security/ssl/DefaultSslEngineFactory.java#L509&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;supported in the codebase&lt;/a&gt; but setting an ssl.key.password is currently enforced by createKeystore (on DefaultSslEngineFactory). I was unable to find a reason for this, so I wonder if this limitation could simply be removed:&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/pera/kafka/commit/8df2feab5fc6955cf8c89a7d132f05d8f562e16b&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/pera/kafka/commit/8df2feab5fc6955cf8c89a7d132f05d8f562e16b&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</description>
